# Doctor Frontend Environment Configuration
# 
# Backend API URL - Leave empty for local development (auto-detects localhost:5000)
# Set this for remote backend or production deployments
VITE_API_BASE_URL=

# ============================================
# DEPLOYMENT GUIDES
# ============================================
#
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (backend on same machine):
#   - Leave VITE_API_BASE_URL empty (or comment it out)
#   - Frontend: npm run dev (runs on http://localhost:5173)
#   - Backend: npm run dev (runs on http://localhost:5000)
#   - Auto-Config: Backend CORS_ORIGINS should be empty
#
# OTHER DEVICE ON LOCAL NETWORK:
#   - Backend machine: ipconfig (Windows) or ifconfig (Linux/Mac) → note the IP
#   - Set: VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://[BACKEND_IP]:5000
#     Example: VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://192.168.1.100:5000
#   - Backend: Update CORS_ORIGINS to match frontend origin
#     Example: CORS_ORIGINS=http://192.168.1.101:5173
#
# VERCEL DEPLOYMENT:
#   - Deploy backend as separate Vercel project or service
#   - Set: VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-backend-url.vercel.app
#   - Backend: Set CORS_ORIGINS=https://your-frontend-url.vercel.app
#
# SAME-DOMAIN DEPLOYMENT (frontend & backend on same domain):
#   - Leave VITE_API_BASE_URL empty
#   - Use relative /api paths (works when served from same origin)
#   - Backend & frontend served from same domain/subdomain
